President Obama met with several senior officials, including Secretary Napolitano, Secretary Chu, Secretary Salazar, Administrator Jackson, Administrator Lubchenco, National Incident Commander Admiral Thad Allen, Assistant to the President for Energy and Climate Change Carol Browner, to receive a briefing on the administration's response to the BP Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill. The briefing covered ongoing efforts to fight the oil near shore and offshore, cleanup of impacted shorelines, well integrity testing, relief well progress, monitoring of severe weather in the Gulf, and data collection and analysis by the federal science team. The President emphasized the need to be prepared for any scenarios related to the potential development of a tropical storm in the Gulf.